msgctxt "mn150:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 150 "
msgstr "Middle Discourses 150 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn150:0.2"
msgid "Nagaravindeyyasutta "
msgstr "With the People of Nagaravinda "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: nya1, pts-vp-pli3.291, sc1
msgctxt "mn150:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "mn150:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosalesu cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ yena nagaravindaṃ nāma kosalānaṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ gāmo tadavasari. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was wandering in the land of the Kosalans together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants when he arrived at a village of the Kosalan brahmins named Nagaravinda. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya2
msgctxt "mn150:2.1"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho nagaravindeyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā: "
msgstr "The brahmins and householders of Nagaravinda heard, "

msgctxt "mn150:2.2"
msgid "“samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo sakyaputto sakyakulā pabbajito kosalesu cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ nagaravindaṃ anuppatto. "
msgstr "“It seems the ascetic Gotama—a Sakyan, gone forth from a Sakyan family—while wandering in the land of the Kosalans has arrived at Nagaravinda, together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants. "

msgctxt "mn150:2.3"
msgid "Taṃ kho pana bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato: "
msgstr "He has this good reputation: "

msgctxt "mn150:2.4"
msgid "‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti. "
msgstr "‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’ "

msgctxt "mn150:2.5"
msgid "So imaṃ lokaṃ sadevakaṃ samārakaṃ sabrahmakaṃ sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiṃ pajaṃ sadevamanussaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedeti. "
msgstr "He has realized with his own insight this world—with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—and he makes it known to others. "

msgctxt "mn150:2.6"
msgid "So dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ, kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāseti. "
msgstr "He teaches Dhamma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And he reveals a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure. "

msgctxt "mn150:2.7"
msgid "Sādhu kho pana tathārūpānaṃ arahataṃ dassanaṃ hotī”ti. "
msgstr "It’s good to see such perfected ones.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya3, sc2
msgctxt "mn150:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho nagaravindeyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā appekacce bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Appekacce bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu; sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Appekacce yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Appekacce bhagavato santike nāmagottaṃ sāvetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Appekacce tuṇhībhūtā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinne kho nagaravindeyyake brāhmaṇagahapatike bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then the brahmins and householders of Nagaravinda went up to the Buddha. Before sitting down to one side, some bowed, some exchanged greetings and polite conversation, some held up their joined palms toward the Buddha, some announced their name and clan, while some kept silent. The Buddha said to them: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya4, pts-vp-pli3.292, sc3
msgctxt "mn150:4.1"
msgid "“Sace vo, gahapatayo, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ puccheyyuṃ: "
msgstr "“Householders, if wanderers who follow another path were to ask you: "

msgctxt "mn150:4.2"
msgid "‘kathaṃbhūtā, gahapatayo, samaṇabrāhmaṇā na sakkātabbā na garukātabbā na mānetabbā na pūjetabbā’ti? "
msgstr "‘What kind of ascetic or brahmin doesn’t deserve honor, respect, reverence, and veneration?’ "

msgctxt "mn150:4.3"
msgid "Evaṃ puṭṭhā tumhe, gahapatayo, tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ evaṃ byākareyyātha: "
msgstr "You should answer them: "

# NOTE: BB’s “now righteously, now unrighteously” is incorrect: cp SN 1.7, etc.
msgctxt "mn150:4.4"
msgid "‘ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā cakkhuviññeyyesu rūpesu avītarāgā avītadosā avītamohā, ajjhattaṃ avūpasantacittā, samavisamaṃ caranti kāyena vācāya manasā, evarūpā samaṇabrāhmaṇā na sakkātabbā na garukātabbā na mānetabbā na pūjetabbā. "
msgstr "‘There are ascetics and brahmins who are not free of greed, hate, and delusion for sights known by the eye, who are not peaceful inside, and who conduct themselves badly among the good by way of body, speech, and mind. They don’t deserve honor, respect, reverence, and veneration. "

msgctxt "mn150:4.5"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "mn150:4.6"
msgid "Mayampi hi cakkhuviññeyyesu rūpesu avītarāgā avītadosā avītamohā, ajjhattaṃ avūpasantacittā, samavisamaṃ carāma kāyena vācāya manasā, tesaṃ no samacariyampi hetaṃ uttari apassataṃ. "
msgstr "Because we ourselves are not free of these things, so we do not see that they have any higher good conduct than us. "

msgctxt "mn150:4.7"
msgid "Tasmā te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā na sakkātabbā na garukātabbā na mānetabbā na pūjetabbā. "
msgstr "That’s why they don’t deserve honor, respect, reverence, and veneration. "

msgctxt "mn150:4.8"
msgid "Ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā sotaviññeyyesu saddesu … "
msgstr "There are ascetics and brahmins who are not free of greed, hate, and delusion for sounds known by the ear … "

msgctxt "mn150:4.9"
msgid "ghānaviññeyyesu gandhesu … "
msgstr "smells known by the nose … "

msgctxt "mn150:4.10"
msgid "jivhāviññeyyesu rasesu … "
msgstr "tastes known by the tongue… "

msgctxt "mn150:4.11"
msgid "kāyaviññeyyesu phoṭṭhabbesu … "
msgstr "touches known by the body … "

msgctxt "mn150:4.12"
msgid "manoviññeyyesu dhammesu avītarāgā avītadosā avītamohā, ajjhattaṃ avūpasantacittā, samavisamaṃ caranti kāyena vācāya manasā, evarūpā samaṇabrāhmaṇā na sakkātabbā na garukātabbā na mānetabbā na pūjetabbā. "
msgstr "thoughts known by the mind, who are not peaceful inside, and who conduct themselves badly among the good by way of body, speech, and mind. They don’t deserve honor, respect, reverence, and veneration. "

msgctxt "mn150:4.13"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "mn150:4.14"
msgid "Mayampi hi manoviññeyyesu dhammesu avītarāgā avītadosā avītamohā, ajjhattaṃ avūpasantacittā, samavisamaṃ carāma kāyena vācāya manasā, tesaṃ no samacariyampi hetaṃ uttari apassataṃ. "
msgstr "Because we ourselves are not free of these things, so we do not see that they have any higher good conduct than us. "

msgctxt "mn150:4.15"
msgid "Tasmā te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā na sakkātabbā na garukātabbā na mānetabbā na pūjetabbā’ti. "
msgstr "That’s why they don’t deserve honor, respect, reverence, and veneration.’ "

msgctxt "mn150:4.16"
msgid "Evaṃ puṭṭhā tumhe, gahapatayo, tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ evaṃ byākareyyātha. "
msgstr "When questioned by wanderers who follow other paths, that’s how you should answer them. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya5, sc4
msgctxt "mn150:5.1"
msgid "Sace pana vo, gahapatayo, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ puccheyyuṃ: "
msgstr "If wanderers who follow other paths were to ask you: "

msgctxt "mn150:5.2"
msgid "‘kathaṃbhūtā, gahapatayo, samaṇabrāhmaṇā sakkātabbā garukātabbā mānetabbā pūjetabbā’ti? "
msgstr "‘What kind of ascetic or brahmin deserves honor, respect, reverence, and veneration?’ "

msgctxt "mn150:5.3"
msgid "Evaṃ puṭṭhā tumhe, gahapatayo, tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ evaṃ byākareyyātha: "
msgstr "You should answer them: "

